oc:kn_2a36736f a oc:Command,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When testing regex patterns before using in a rule" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "bash" ;
    oc:directiveContent "python3 -c \"import re; print(re.search(r'your_pattern', 'test text'))\"" .

oc:kn_2c424622 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Standard ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating any hookify rule" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Rule files must be stored at .claude/hookify.{descriptive-name}.local.md with YAML frontmatter containing required fields: name (kebab-case, verb-prefixed), enabled (boolean), event (bash|file|stop|prompt|all), and either pattern (simple regex) or conditions (array of field/operator/pattern objects)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "The hookify engine reads files matching this exact naming convention and frontmatter schema to register active rules." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_353aef0d a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When using the advanced multi-condition format" ;
    oc:directiveContent "All conditions in a conditions array must match (AND logic) for the rule to trigger. There is no OR logic between conditions — use regex alternation (|) within a single pattern instead." ;
    oc:hasRationale "This is a fundamental limitation of the conditions format that affects how rules should be structured." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_3787643d a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing regex patterns for rule conditions" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not write overly broad patterns like `log` (matches login, dialog, catalog) or overly specific patterns like `rm -rf /tmp` (only exact match). Prefer scoped patterns like `console\\.log\\(` or `rm\\s+-rf`." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Overly broad patterns cause false positives and rule fatigue; overly specific patterns miss legitimate matches." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_41ac2ce3 a oc:Idempotency,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When modifying existing rules" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Rules are read dynamically on each tool use — editing, disabling (enabled: false), or deleting a rule file takes effect immediately on the next tool invocation with no restart required." .

oc:kn_458078dd a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Minimum viable hookify rule template" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """---
name: my-rule
enabled: true
event: bash
pattern: dangerous_command
---

Warning message here""" .

oc:kn_61e95013 a oc:CodePattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "Advanced multi-condition hookify rule with AND logic" ;
    oc:codeLanguage "markdown" ;
    oc:directiveContent """---
name: warn-env-file-edits
enabled: true
event: file
conditions:
  - field: file_path
    operator: regex_match
    pattern: \\.env$
  - field: new_text
    operator: contains
    pattern: API_KEY
---

You're adding an API key to a .env file. Ensure this file is in .gitignore!""" .

oc:kn_81ac8eb6 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing regex patterns in YAML frontmatter" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use unquoted patterns in YAML frontmatter to avoid double-backslash escaping issues. Unquoted `pattern: \\s` works as-is, while quoted `\"pattern\"` requires `\\\\s`." ;
    oc:hasRationale "YAML quoted strings trigger additional escaping layers that produce incorrect regex patterns." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_8b57f2e8 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When writing the markdown body of a hookify rule" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Rule message bodies should explain what was detected, why it is problematic, and suggest alternatives or best practices. Use markdown formatting (bold, lists, warnings) for clarity." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Effective messages help Claude understand the context and make better decisions, rather than just being warned." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_98522d00 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Prerequisite ;
    oc:directiveContent "The .claude/ directory must exist in the project root. Add .claude/*.local.md to .gitignore to prevent committing local rules." .

oc:kn_b29fcd6d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:OutputFormat ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating a hookify rule file" ;
    oc:directiveContent """.claude/hookify.{descriptive-name}.local.md

Frontmatter fields:
- name: kebab-case, verb-prefixed (required)
- enabled: true|false (required)
- event: bash|file|stop|prompt|all (required)
- action: warn|block (optional, default warn)
- pattern: regex string (simple rules) OR conditions: array of {field, operator, pattern} (complex rules)

Body: Markdown message shown on trigger""" ;
    oc:templateVariables "action",
        "conditions",
        "descriptive-name",
        "enabled",
        "event",
        "name",
        "pattern" .

oc:kn_b4209a9f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When creating a new hookify rule" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Identify unwanted behavior 2. Determine which tool is involved (Bash, Edit, etc.) 3. Choose event type (bash, file, stop, etc.) 4. Write regex pattern 5. Create .claude/hookify.{name}.local.md file in project root 6. Test immediately — rules are read dynamically on next tool use" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_b6d446ce a oc:KnowledgeNode,
